---
description: conda envs for this repo
alwaysApply: true
---

Use **conda ``swebench311``** when running **distributed SWE-bench** and **HF model servers** (``distributed_swebench_inference.py``, ``start_server.py``) so PyTorch matches the host NVIDIA driver. After activating, point child servers at that interpreter:

```bash
conda activate swebench311
export SPARSE_ATTENTION_SERVER_PYTHON=$(which python)
```

If you launch the driver script with ``uv run`` or another venv, keep ``SPARSE_ATTENTION_SERVER_PYTHON`` set so ``start_server`` subprocesses still use ``swebench311``.

For other repo work, you may use **``sparse_attention_hub``** when that is the project default:

```bash
conda activate sparse_attention_hub
```
